Hey,

273
00:22:35.044 --> 00:22:36.004
soldiers!

274
00:22:36.379 --> 00:22:37.463
Stop that snoozing!

275
00:22:37.714 --> 00:22:38.673
Reveille!

276
00:22:40.425 --> 00:22:41.384
Konstantin,

277
00:22:41.718 --> 00:22:42.760
come here.

278
00:22:43.803 --> 00:22:45.179
Come on guys, hurry up.

279
00:22:45.805 --> 00:22:47.265
We haven't got far to go.

280
00:22:55.773 --> 00:22:56.774
And?

281
00:22:58.735 --> 00:22:59.777
No-one out there.

282
00:23:04.115 --> 00:23:05.199
Not a soul.

283
00:23:21.340 --> 00:23:23.009
Check the barn, Kostya.

284
00:23:52.371 --> 00:23:53.456
Call the guys.

285
00:24:15.686 --> 00:24:16.813
What are you doing?

286
00:24:19.273 --> 00:24:20.441
-Are you nuts?
-Hey!


287
00:24:21.651 --> 00:24:22.860
What the hell's going on?

288
00:24:23.111 --> 00:24:24.445
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

289
00:24:24.821 --> 00:24:26.447
Just calm down!

290
00:24:26.739 --> 00:24:28.157
Are you crazy?

291
00:24:32.912 --> 00:24:35.581
Don't interfere, Pops!
Did you see what he did?


292
00:24:35.873 --> 00:24:37.125
What are you doing?

293
00:24:38.334 --> 00:24:39.293
Idiot!

294
00:24:40.336 --> 00:24:42.004
He saved your damned life!

295
00:24:43.214 --> 00:24:45.383
My friend never kept vodka here.

296
00:24:46.175 --> 00:24:49.554
Everything's poisoned. A trap laid by
the fascists for the Partisans,


297
00:24:49.720 --> 00:24:51.139
or maybe it's that avenger.

298
00:24:51.764 --> 00:24:53.224
Ten people in the village...

299
00:24:53.850 --> 00:24:56.811
have died after stupidly drinking
this vile liquid.


300
00:24:56.978 --> 00:24:59.897
You should thank him
for saving your life. Not fighting him.


301
00:25:00.064 --> 00:25:01.023
Idiot.

302
00:25:07.321 --> 00:25:08.948
Why would they do that?

303
00:25:15.371 --> 00:25:17.832
Don't look so pleased.
It's all been poisoned.


304
00:25:18.207 --> 00:25:19.458
Even the vodka.

305
00:25:20.084 --> 00:25:21.711
A gift from them Germans.

306
00:25:22.378 --> 00:25:24.714
When are we going to eat properly?

307
00:25:26.048 --> 00:25:28.134
Try to find some clean clothes for me.

308
00:25:28.384 --> 00:25:30.678
Why are you standing there?
Look in the chest.


309
00:25:31.012 --> 00:25:31.971
So good.

310
00:25:32.763 --> 00:25:33.931
So good.

311
00:25:47.153 --> 00:25:48.988
What's up? What you looking at?

312
00:25:49.280 --> 00:25:51.157
Never seen a pregnant woman before?

313
00:25:57.747 --> 00:25:58.706
How?

314
00:25:59.707 --> 00:26:01.083
What are you talking about?

315
00:26:02.543 --> 00:26:04.587
Don't you know how babies are made?

316
00:26:14.722 --> 00:26:16.349
I'm such a fool.

317
00:26:16.682 --> 00:26:17.683
Will this do?

318
00:26:18.267 --> 00:26:19.352
That'll do it.

319
00:26:44.210 --> 00:26:45.419
Three days ago,

320
00:26:45.628 --> 00:26:47.046
six of our best men
were killed in Nizovskaya.


321
00:26:47.255 --> 00:26:49.173
Then, in the village of Ivanovo,

322
00:26:49.840 --> 00:26:51.259
two of our men were killed.

323
00:26:53.261 --> 00:26:54.637
In the last big battle...

324
00:26:56.180 --> 00:26:57.682
that took place in the village

325
00:26:58.140 --> 00:26:59.517
of Lenskoye.

326
00:27:00.434 --> 00:27:02.728
-They killed sixteen men.
-Do you like 'Banya'?


327
00:27:02.937 --> 00:27:04.939
-Excuse me?
-Banya.


328
00:27:05.398 --> 00:27:07.233
Like a sauna, but with steam.

329
00:27:09.026 --> 00:27:11.487
To be honest, not really.

330
00:27:12.113 --> 00:27:14.198
What, not even in such a frost?

331
00:27:16.075 --> 00:27:18.411
Have you heard of '
Black Banya' at all?

332
00:27:19.328 --> 00:27:21.455
Yes. There's one nearby.

333
00:27:22.790 --> 00:27:24.333
German sauna is nice,

334
00:27:24.542 --> 00:27:27.086
but 'Black Banya" is a real challenge.

335
00:27:27.295 --> 00:27:28.879
Banya's a passion.

336
00:27:29.255 --> 00:27:32.550
In weather such as this,
it warms you to the very bone.


337
00:27:33.509 --> 00:27:35.636
Which says a lot about the Russians.

338
00:27:36.512 --> 00:27:38.055
You should study your enemy.

339
00:27:38.639 --> 00:27:39.724
How they live.

340
00:27:40.016 --> 00:27:41.183
How they think.

341
00:27:41.934 --> 00:27:43.227
How they wash themselves.

342
00:27:43.519 --> 00:27:44.562
[Braun laughs]

343
00:27:45.062 --> 00:27:47.023
The Russians love extremes.

344
00:27:47.231 --> 00:27:48.941
They have a rather hard life.

345
00:27:49.108 --> 00:27:51.819
[Klein laughs] Well,
they have no choice really do they?


346
00:27:52.028 --> 00:27:53.571
[Braun laughs] Oh but they do.

347
00:27:54.030 --> 00:27:55.281
Where is that bath house?

348
00:27:55.489 --> 00:27:56.741
Not far from here.

349
00:27:57.158 --> 00:27:58.701
So, is this sector cleared?

350
00:27:59.201 --> 00:28:00.870
Yes sir, this is my sector.

351
00:28:01.203 --> 00:28:02.455
No enemy here.

352
00:28:02.788 --> 00:28:04.123
Well, then let's go.

353
00:28:05.082 --> 00:28:06.042
Comrade!

354
00:28:06.917 --> 00:28:07.877
Stop!

355
00:28:09.962 --> 00:28:11.589
<i>Don't move anything on the table.</i>

356
00:28:11.922 --> 00:28:13.924
Now listen carefully to the orders.

357
00:28:14.675 --> 00:28:15.926
We'll go to the village,

358
00:28:16.218 --> 00:28:17.678
and we will look for products,

359
00:28:17.928 --> 00:28:19.347
such as matches and the like.

360
00:28:19.847 --> 00:28:20.806
After this,

361
00:28:21.349 --> 00:28:22.391
we'll move on.

362
00:28:22.558 --> 00:28:23.684
You've time for a rest.

363
00:28:23.851 --> 00:28:24.810
No.

364
00:28:25.102 --> 00:28:26.187
I'll go with you.

365
00:28:27.271 --> 00:28:29.148
-You'll stay with her.
-[Simpleton] Me?


366
00:28:30.024 --> 00:28:30.983
No, him.

367
00:28:31.359 --> 00:28:33.235
Sergeant, nod your head when I speak.

368
00:28:33.527 --> 00:28:34.570
[Sailor] Of course.

369
00:28:36.989 --> 00:28:38.449
[suspenseful music]

370
00:29:19.615 --> 00:29:20.783
[Vera gasps]

371
00:29:25.121 --> 00:29:26.747
[soldiers speaking]

372
00:29:55.276 --> 00:29:57.069
[soldiers shouting]

373
00:30:26.891 --> 00:30:28.058
[Klein] Shit!

374
00:30:30.352 --> 00:30:31.479
It's steamy here.

375
00:30:31.770 --> 00:30:32.730
[soldier 2] No.

376
00:30:33.647 --> 00:30:34.648
[Klein] God!

377
00:30:43.616 --> 00:30:44.742
Good job.

378
00:30:47.286 --> 00:30:48.370
[Klein] Come in.

379
00:30:54.502 --> 00:30:55.878
What are you staring at?

380
00:30:59.924 --> 00:31:01.550
How do you like my still-life?

381
00:31:01.967 --> 00:31:03.802
-Your idea?
-Yes,


382
00:31:04.011 --> 00:31:05.846
and it seems to work as well.

383
00:31:06.347 --> 00:31:08.557
We killed four soldiers last week.

384
00:31:16.357 --> 00:31:18.150
Look at this, Commander.

385
00:31:19.401 --> 00:31:21.362
The Russians pray to two gods.

386
00:31:23.322 --> 00:31:25.366
You think it's any different for us?

387
00:31:26.534 --> 00:31:28.285
I'm sorry. Clear the table.

388
00:31:32.164 --> 00:31:34.959
The food here is making me hungry.
Organize something, Klein.


389
00:31:35.376 --> 00:31:37.086
Already on the way.

390
00:31:37.628 --> 00:31:39.129
Boys, hurry it up!

391
00:31:57.773 --> 00:31:59.108
Be quiet. Stop.

392
00:31:59.692 --> 00:32:00.651
Stop there.

393
00:32:00.901 --> 00:32:03.028
-It's the Germans.
-[Pops] Holy shit.


394
00:32:03.320 --> 00:32:04.321
Where's Vera?

395
00:32:04.488 --> 00:32:05.447
Back at the house.

396
00:32:05.698 --> 00:32:07.032
You disobeyed my order.

397
00:32:07.783 --> 00:32:10.452
You want me to fight alone,
is that it? Just me, eh?


398
00:32:12.079 --> 00:32:14.498
30 Germans, and I've got 30 bullets.

399
00:32:14.873 --> 00:32:16.625
I just stepped out to take a piss--

400
00:32:16.792 --> 00:32:18.043
Looking for moonshine.

401
00:32:18.252 --> 00:32:19.878
You really are a son of a bitch.

402
00:32:20.296 --> 00:32:22.172
So what if I was? 
What's your problem?

403
00:32:23.299 --> 00:32:24.675
What you gonna do, shoot me?

404
00:32:30.431 --> 00:32:32.057
So what do we do now?

405
00:32:45.195 --> 00:32:46.155
Hey,

406
00:32:46.488 --> 00:32:47.448
Gunther!

407
00:32:47.948 --> 00:32:49.742
Here, look at this.

408
00:32:50.075 --> 00:32:51.076
[Gunther laughs]

409
00:32:51.910 --> 00:32:53.120
A present...

410
00:32:53.871 --> 00:32:55.623
from the Eastern Front.

411
00:32:58.208 --> 00:33:00.794
[soldiers laughing]

412
00:33:01.128 --> 00:33:03.088
We should take a photo.

413
00:33:04.465 --> 00:33:07.092
-Great. Take your places.
-Hey, give it to me.


414
00:33:07.593 --> 00:33:08.719
Hold it.

415
00:33:08.969 --> 00:33:10.346
Are we taking this photo?

416
00:33:11.096 --> 00:33:12.473
Right, all stand together.

417
00:33:13.265 --> 00:33:15.142
All right, now. Yeah.

418
00:33:16.852 --> 00:33:18.520
Can't you hold the piglet eh?

419
00:33:20.314 --> 00:33:22.024
[soldier laughing]

420
00:33:22.941 --> 00:33:24.109
Let it go.

421
00:33:24.568 --> 00:33:26.195
No. Why? You wanna dance with it?

422
00:33:28.030 --> 00:33:29.990
A dance with a Russian beauty.

423
00:33:30.157 --> 00:33:31.325
[soldiers laughing]

424
00:33:36.163 --> 00:33:39.500
[soldiers singing]

425
00:33:46.090 --> 00:33:48.217
[tense music]

426
00:33:49.551 --> 00:33:50.636
Was that Vera?

427
00:33:51.470 --> 00:33:53.138
Just them morons having fun.

428
00:33:58.977 --> 00:34:00.771
One doesn't play with food.

429
00:34:09.196 --> 00:34:11.198
You have problems with discipline.

430
00:34:11.573 --> 00:34:13.409
Don't be so strict with them.

431
00:34:13.659 --> 00:34:16.370
The soldiers are tired and need some fun.

432
00:34:17.413 --> 00:34:19.164
Not the soldiers.

433
00:34:19.498 --> 00:34:21.500
Only officers are entitled.

434
00:34:29.758 --> 00:34:31.093
Three men in the trench.

435
00:34:35.013 --> 00:34:37.474
Sixteen in the yard.
Who knows how many inside.


436
00:34:38.809 --> 00:34:39.893
Not 30, for sure.

437
00:34:40.060 --> 00:34:41.019
Oh, come on.

438
00:34:43.522 --> 00:34:44.481
We'll wait.

439
00:34:45.357 --> 00:34:46.316
How long?

440
00:34:48.360 --> 00:34:50.654
Pops, keep your eyes on the farm,

441
00:34:50.863 --> 00:34:52.781
and report about any movements you see.

442
00:34:53.031 --> 00:34:55.701
-With God's will, they'll leave.
-And if they don't go?


443
00:34:56.702 --> 00:34:58.287
Then we'll act accordingly.

444
00:34:58.996 --> 00:35:00.205
Check the ammunition.

445
00:35:00.497 --> 00:35:01.457
We move out at dusk,

446
00:35:01.749 --> 00:35:02.958
if she's still alive.

447
00:35:12.926 --> 00:35:14.178
Tell me, Klein,

448
00:35:15.888 --> 00:35:17.973
do you also believe in this Ghost?

449
00:35:19.516 --> 00:35:20.476
Don't know.

450
00:35:20.684 --> 00:35:22.728
To be honest, I don't. But...

451
00:35:23.020 --> 00:35:24.313
according to witnesses,

452
00:35:24.646 --> 00:35:26.148
he comes out of the blue,

453
00:35:26.440 --> 00:35:28.692
and is unusually strong and brave.

454
00:35:33.781 --> 00:35:35.616
The Russians have a saying,

455
00:35:37.075 --> 00:35:38.994
"Fear has big eyes".

456
00:35:40.454 --> 00:35:43.123
And this barbarous ritual,
with the torn-off epaulets,


457
00:35:43.957 --> 00:35:46.084
it is simply a provocation
by the Partisans.


458
00:35:46.293 --> 00:35:48.170
I don't think
the peasants would lie.


459
00:35:49.421 --> 00:35:51.340
People don't lie
at the threshold of death.


460
00:35:55.177 --> 00:35:56.762
-[Vera gasps]
- It is okay.


461
00:35:57.805 --> 00:35:59.598
If he is really as you describe him,

462
00:36:00.015 --> 00:36:01.475
then I'd like to meet him.

463
00:36:04.436 --> 00:36:06.647
It's uncomfortable here
'cause it's so cold.


464
00:36:07.022 --> 00:36:07.981
[Klein] Gunther,

465
00:36:08.273 --> 00:36:09.233
get to work.

466
00:36:09.525 --> 00:36:10.484
Yes, sir.

467
00:36:14.321 --> 00:36:16.240
[soldiers talking]

468
00:36:18.242 --> 00:36:20.285
Koch, when is it ready?

469
00:36:20.702 --> 00:36:21.995
Don't you worry.

470
00:36:22.663 --> 00:36:24.665
-It's all getting sorted.
-Get a move on!


471
00:36:24.915 --> 00:36:26.083
I'm getting hungry.

472
00:36:26.458 --> 00:36:27.835
Can't wait much longer.

473
00:36:28.001 --> 00:36:30.337
It would go quicker
if you stopped pestering me.


474
00:36:44.768 --> 00:36:47.104
[Pops] Can't see a thing
through this damn snow.


475
00:36:50.357 --> 00:36:51.817
Hey, frozen boy.

476
00:36:52.401 --> 00:36:53.694
Come over here.

477
00:37:00.492 --> 00:37:01.451
Here.

478
00:37:01.952 --> 00:37:03.036
Now you watch.

479
00:37:03.829 --> 00:37:05.539
I can't see well from this far.

480
00:37:07.374 --> 00:37:09.084
Make sure you pay attention.

481
00:37:10.294 --> 00:37:12.212
-Firing up the bathhouse.
-You're sure?


482
00:37:12.504 --> 00:37:13.547
The bathhouse?

483
00:37:14.840 --> 00:37:16.049
The Germans?

484
00:37:17.175 --> 00:37:18.719
Well, I'll be damned.

485
00:37:20.679 --> 00:37:22.389
I hope you roast here, Braun.

486
00:37:24.099 --> 00:37:25.350
[Gunther sighs]

487
00:37:28.604 --> 00:37:30.647
-What's wrong with his eye?
-Huh?


488
00:37:31.023 --> 00:37:32.024
Battle wound?

489
00:37:32.357 --> 00:37:33.901
No, it's not a battle wound.

490
00:37:34.359 --> 00:37:35.444
As a kid,

491
00:37:36.153 --> 00:37:38.614
he was stealing apples
from someone's garden.


492
00:37:38.906 --> 00:37:41.408
The owner came out
and shot his rifle in the air.


493
00:37:41.617 --> 00:37:42.910
The kids, they jumped down

494
00:37:43.118 --> 00:37:44.244
from the apple tree.

495
00:37:44.578 --> 00:37:46.455
But he fell, from the very top.

496
00:37:46.955 --> 00:37:48.624
A branch went through his eye.

497
00:37:52.502 --> 00:37:53.545
And it was...

498
00:37:53.879 --> 00:37:54.880
my garden.

499
00:37:57.507 --> 00:37:58.717
So now I kinda...

500
00:37:59.635 --> 00:38:01.136
feel responsible for him,

501
00:38:02.012 --> 00:38:03.180
in front of the Lord.

502
00:38:03.388 --> 00:38:04.932
It's just how it is.

503
00:38:06.433 --> 00:38:08.018
[Pops laughs] But it turns out,

504
00:38:08.435 --> 00:38:09.853
he's an excellent hunter.

505
00:38:11.939 --> 00:38:13.023
[Pops laughs]

506
00:38:13.231 --> 00:38:15.067
What are we doing just sitting here?

507
00:38:15.400 --> 00:38:16.735
And what do you suggest?

508
00:38:17.611 --> 00:38:18.654
Have a death wish?

509
00:38:21.114 --> 00:38:22.824
We need to act cleverly,

510
00:38:23.700 --> 00:38:25.369
like, say, that Ghost.

511
00:38:26.328 --> 00:38:27.287
Who?

512
00:38:28.205 --> 00:38:29.414
The Red Ghost.

513
00:38:31.041 --> 00:38:34.378
The sauna is ready in one hour.

514
00:38:35.212 --> 00:38:38.215
If I were you, I would think twice
before going to the sauna.


515
00:38:38.465 --> 00:38:40.133
Maybe it's not a good idea.

516
00:38:40.550 --> 00:38:42.678
-Firstly, it's "Black Banya'.
-[tense music]


517
00:38:44.471 --> 00:38:46.306
Secondly, you are not me.

518
00:38:46.473 --> 00:38:47.432
You misunderstood--

519
00:38:47.599 --> 00:38:49.893
Thirdly,
you don't have authority to interrupt!


520
00:38:50.102 --> 00:38:51.269
Yes, Commander.

521
00:38:53.188 --> 00:38:54.147
Get up!

522
00:38:54.314 --> 00:38:55.941
[tense music intensifies]

523
00:38:56.733 --> 00:38:57.693
[Vera gasps]

524
00:38:59.653 --> 00:39:01.530
This is horrible work

525
00:39:01.697 --> 00:39:04.074
and the worst unit
I have ever seen in my life!


526
00:39:04.992 --> 00:39:08.370
I'm not at all interested in your opinion
about what I should,


527
00:39:08.578 --> 00:39:09.705
or shouldn't do.

528
00:39:10.372 --> 00:39:12.666
If you can't understand this,

529
00:39:12.958 --> 00:39:15.794
then your place is not here,
but outside in the yard,


530
00:39:16.336 --> 00:39:18.255
with the pigs.

531
00:39:18.630 --> 00:39:21.174
-Clear enough?
-Yes, Commander!


532
00:39:21.341 --> 00:39:23.301
It won't happen again, Commander!

533
00:39:24.678 --> 00:39:25.637
Good.

534
00:39:27.514 --> 00:39:28.932
Then let us leave this subject,

535
00:39:29.099 --> 00:39:30.934
or our young soldier will pass out.

536
00:39:32.436 --> 00:39:33.395
Tell me,

537
00:39:34.980 --> 00:39:36.064
what's your name?

538
00:39:37.691 --> 00:39:39.443
-Gunther.
-Gunther.


539
00:39:44.406 --> 00:39:45.365
Take a seat.

540
00:39:54.499 --> 00:39:56.835
He is not well in his company.

541
00:39:57.627 --> 00:39:59.546
Yeah, that's true.

542
00:40:01.506 --> 00:40:04.968
Do you know how
they call our Commander?


543
00:40:07.387 --> 00:40:08.346
Braun?

544
00:40:10.307 --> 00:40:11.475
Hangman Braun.

545
00:40:12.642 --> 00:40:15.228
Do you know why they would give him...

546
00:40:15.562 --> 00:40:18.398
a nickname such as that, then?

547
00:40:18.940 --> 00:40:20.734
[Schmidt] I don't want to know it!

548
00:40:21.318 --> 00:40:23.236
Anyway, it's better to hunt for

